The paper proposes a new method for multi-objective Bayesian optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves using entropy to evaluate the Pareto-frontier in the output space, which could also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper includes numerical experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests a potential application in neural networks (cs.NE).
